The '''Frascati Tokamak Upgrade''' is a [[tokamak]] operating at [[Frascati]], [[Italy]]. Building on the [[Frascati Tokamak]] experiment, FTU is a compact, high-magnetic-field tokamak ('''B'''<sub>θ</sub> = 8 [[Tesla (unit)|T]]). It began operation in 1990 and has since achieved operating goals of 1.6 [[megaampere|MA]] at 8 T and average electron density greater than 4{{e|20}} per cubic meter. The poloidal section of FTU is circular, with a limiter.
