'''''Last Drinks: The Impact of the Northern Territory Intervention''''' is a 2008 [[Quarterly Essay]] by [[Australian]] journalist [[Paul Toohey]].  Toohey critiques the Australian government’s intervention in remote indigenous communities in the Northern Territory, which began in 2007, and aimed to protect indigenous children from a “national emergency” of child [[sexual abuse]].<ref>[http://www.greenleft.org.au/2008/756/39069 Paul Toohey: Mixed messaged and malign motivations] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080829173132/http://www.greenleft.org.au/2008/756/39069 |date=2008-08-29 }}</ref> ''Last Drinks'' won the 2008 [[Walkley Award]] for "Coverage of Indigenous Affairs".<ref>[http://www.quarterlyessay.com/qe/pastissues/index.php QE 30 Last Drinks] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218214240/http://www.quarterlyessay.com/qe/pastissues/index.php |date=2008-12-18 }}</ref>

